<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>Spanish - Gu&#237;a para Localizaci&#243;n de Fallas del Sistema El&#233;ctrico - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400,
        7300, 7400, 7500, 8500, 8600 - POWER STEERING PUMP: VICKERS (LUK) V10NF AND V20NF - REMOVE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>REMOVE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="0">
            <title>BELT DRIVEN PUMP</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Block wheels and set parking brake.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Drain power steering fluid.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove pressure and return lines, and pump supply hose (remote mounted reservoir) from
                    the pump.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Release belt tension and remove the belts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the bolt that secures the pump pulley to the pump shaft.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the pulley.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen the bolts that secure the pump mounting brackets to the engine front cover.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the nuts that secure the power steering pump to the pump brackets.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the pump.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Plug all removed units and cap all lines to prevent getting any dirt into the system.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
